Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.34,0:00:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,TRACE. Class one through nine sustainment estimates in seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.34,0:00:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,LOGCOM use case: a logistics estimate informed by doctrine and\Nconsumption rates.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.34,0:00:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Inputs: unit type, personnel, days, climate, opscale.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.34,0:00:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Synthetic GCSS-MC depots and MCWP four-eleven planning rates load\Nlocally - no data movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.34,0:00:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A two-step agentic pipeline produces the full Class one through nine\Nestimate.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.88,0:00:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A Kamiwaza-deployed model drafts a one-page Sustainment Estimate\NBrief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.47,0:00:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Daily lbs-equivalent stacked across all nine classes. Sources per\Nclass.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.49,0:00:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Top depots per class - on-hand quantity and percent of window covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.61,0:00:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Set KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL and the same code runs inside the wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.61,0:01:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Powered by the Kamiwaza Stack. Deploy in hours, not months.
